$ gcc -fomit-frame-pointer

Do not store the frame pointer in a register for functions that don't need it.
-
This option usually makes the executable smaller and sometimes faster at the cost of easy debuging with → development/tools/gdb[`gdb`].

sa:

  Compare with → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/GCC/options/O_uppercase[`-Os`] which → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/GCC/optimization[optimizes] for size.

  → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/GCC/options
